sections.Biography:
===[[Season 1]]===
[[File:Shaggydog_1x10.jpg|thumb|left|[[Shaggydog]] scares [[Bran Stark|Bran]] and [[Osha]] in the crypts of [[Winterfell]].]]Shaggydog was adopted as a pup with the rest of the Stark direwolves when [[Eddard Stark]] and his entourage came upon the pups and their deceased mother. At the request of [[Jon Snow]], the pups were spared and each Stark child adopted one as their own. Rickon names his direwolf Shaggydog.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Winter is Coming]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Shaggydog leaps out at [[Bran Stark|Bran]] and [[Osha]] in the Stark family crypt, frightening them and causing them to fall over. It is said that Shaggydog should be tied up, but he didn't like it.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Fire and Blood]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 2]]===

After Theon has taken Winterfell, Shaggydog flees with [[Osha]], Bran, [[Rickon Stark|Rickon]], [[Hodor]] and [[Summer]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Old Gods and the New]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; Shaggydog and Summer reunite with the fugitives, who had then hidden inside the crypts of Winterfell, after the castle is [[Sack of Winterfell|sacked]] and put to the torch.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Valar Morghulis]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 3]]===
[[File:Summer,_Shaggydog_3x09_1.png|thumb|[[Shaggydog]] and [[Summer]] observe [[Jon Snow]].]]Shaggydog continues north with Rickon, Osha, Bran, Hodor, Summer. The group is later joined by [[Jojen Reed]] and his sister, [[Meera Reed|Meera]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Dark Wings, Dark Words]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; They stop to rest at a small farm, not realizing there is a group of [[Free Folk|wildlings]] nearby. When a thunderstorm startles Hodor and nearly causes him to give up the group's location to the wildlings, Bran [[warg]]s into Summer who is joined by Shaggydog in killing some of the wildlings. Realizing the dangers they face as they continue north, Bran decides to send Rickon away with Osha and Shaggydog to the protection of [[House Umber]] in order to protect Rickon. The three leave in the middle of the night towards [[Last Hearth]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Rains of Castamere (episode)|The Rains of Castamere]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
